Visualize

Durations by trial and run

s1_subset %>% ggplot(.) +
  aes(x = trial_n, y = dur_s, color=run) +
  #facet_grid(. ~ run) +
  geom_smooth(se = FALSE) +
  geom_point() +
  ggtitle("Motion temporal duration threshold data")
## `geom_smooth()` using method = 'loess' and formula 'y ~ x'

Cumulative performance across runs

s1_subset <- s1_subset %>%
  dplyr::group_by(., run) %>%
  dplyr::arrange(., dur_s) %>%
  dplyr::mutate(., cum_sum = cumsum(corr),
                cum_p = cum_sum/n())

# s1_subset %>% ggplot(.) +
#   aes(x = dur_s, y = cum_p) +
#   facet_grid(. ~ run) +
#   geom_point() +
#   geom_smooth(se = FALSE)  +
#   ggtitle("Motion temporal duration threshold data")
s1_subset %>% ggplot(.) +
  aes(x = dur_s, y = cum_p, color=run) +
  #facet_grid(. ~ run) +
  geom_point() +
  geom_smooth(se = FALSE)  +
  ggtitle("Cumulative p(corr) by duration and run")
## `geom_smooth()` using method = 'loess' and formula 'y ~ x'
